The paper deals with a geometric puzzle involving the construction of rectangles, which suggests that it falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem of maximizing the area covered by the rectangles is a combinatorial optimization problem, which could also place the paper under categories such as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) as it discusses the longstanding conjecture about the maximum area that can be covered by anchored rectangles.
